@startuml
' @id(SEQ-TRACE-REVIEW)
' @ref(USE-TRACE-PARITY)
' @desc(SEQ-TRACE-REVIEW, "Project::review() runs traceability as pass 3 (after ID + security). FORWARD: for every implementable @id (CMP-/SEQ-/DOM-/STM-) on the current side, look up its source_links; if a link's symbol is not found by the syn symbol index for its file, push a forward error. REVERSE: ask the engine for symbols changed since base_revision (git diff --unified=0 base..worktree -- source dirs, hunks mapped to enclosing syn symbols); for each changed symbol with no source_link, classify via the escape hatch — exempt glue -> bucket A (warn), behaviour-bearing -> bucket B (error). matched = forward_ok AND bucket_b_empty (subject to traceability.parity_check).")
' Objective sequence for review pass 3 (cycle 0013). The same engine
' (DOM-SYMBOL-SPAN extraction + git changeset) backs both directions
' and is reused by SEQ-MAP-STATUS.
title Traceability review — pass 3 (objective)

participant "Project::review()" as Review
participant "trace.yml\nsource_links" as Trace
participant "Trace engine\n(git + syn)" as Engine
participant "git" as Git
participant "syn symbol index" as Syn
participant "escape hatch\nclassifier" as Hatch
participant "TraceReport" as Rep

== Forward (whole gated model) ==
loop each implementable @id (CMP-/SEQ-/DOM-/STM-) on current side
  Review -> Trace : source_links for @id
  Trace --> Review : (path, symbol)*
  loop each link
    Review -> Syn : symbol found in path?
    alt resolves
      Syn --> Review : span
    else missing
      Review -> Rep : FORWARD ERROR (diagram points at absent code)
    end
  end
end

== Reverse (changeset since base_revision) ==
Review -> Engine : changed_symbols(base_revision)
Engine -> Git : diff --unified=0 base..worktree -- <source dirs>
Git --> Engine : hunks (file, line ranges)
Engine -> Syn : symbols overlapping hunks
Syn --> Engine : enclosing symbols (+ glue regions)
Engine --> Review : ChangedSymbols
loop each ChangedSymbol with no source_link
  Review -> Hatch : classify(symbol / region)
  alt exempt glue (import, attr, comment)
    Hatch --> Rep : BUCKET A (warn + show)
  else behaviour-bearing
    Hatch --> Rep : BUCKET B (error, blocks)
  end
end
Rep --> Review : matched = forward_ok AND bucket_b_empty
@enduml
